    "For each i, let πi (x) = π i (x -τ) -W i.Suppose that for each i, L i = Lip(π j i), j = 1,..., d andS = s( i (f i, π i)) = i L d i.ThenQ i f i det Dπ i - Q ′ i f i det Dπ i ≤ r d+1 ( √ d + 1)S + r d-1 c d √ S i L d-2 i ∥π i -πi ∥ 2 ℓ ∞ (∂Q).(5.11)Proof.",
    "Let us denote f τ i (x) = f i (x -τ).Since translation by τ is an isometry and since W i is a constant vector, we haveQ ′ i f i det Dπ i dL d = Q i f τ i det Dπ i dL d.Therefore, applying (5.9), we obtainQ i f i det Dπ i - Q ′ i f i det Dπ i ≤ r d+1 1 2 √ d i (Lip(f i) + Lip(f τ i))L d i + r d i |(f i) Q -(f i) Q ′ |L d i + r d-1 c d sup i {|(f i) Q |} i L d i i L d-2 i ∥π i -πi ∥ 2 ℓ ∞ (∂Q).Using that the formal Lipschitz sum is regular, we haveLip(f i) + Lip(f τ i) ≤ 2Lip(f i) ≤ 2, |(f i) Q -(f i) Q ′ | ≤ rLip(f i) ≤ r, sup i |(f i) Q | ≤ 1.Thus, the above estimate impliesQ i f i det Dπ i - Q ′ i f i det Dπ i ≤ r d+1 √ dS + r d rS + r d-1 c d √ S i L d-2 i ∥π i -πi ∥ 2 ℓ ∞ (∂Q),which is equivalent to (5.11).We are now ready to outline in more detail how the estimate (5.11) will be used.",
    "Consider we find a solution to the equationi f i det Dπ i = ρ a.e.",
    "in [0, 1] d.where ρ ∈ L ∞ only attains values 1 and 2.",
    "Suppose further that there is plenty of very small pairs of adjacent cubes Q and Q ′, as in Lemma 5.6 such that ρ = 1 on Q and ρ = 2 on Q ′."
